  "response": "I want to be direct but helpful. There could be several reasons why answers might not get upvoted:\n\n1. Content reasons:\n- Answer lacks depth or detail\n- Doesn't fully address the question\n- Seems generic or superficial\n- Contains errors or inaccuracies\n\n2. Communication reasons:\n- Writing style isn't engaging\n- Poor grammar or formatting\n- Hard to read or understand\n- Doesn't provide clear value\n\n3. Timing/Context reasons:\n- Posted late when few people are viewing\n- Question already has good answers\n- Topic isn't very popular\n\nTo improve, focus on:\n- Providing thorough, accurate information\n- Writing clearly and concisely\n- Using good formatting\n- Adding unique insights\n- Citing sources if relevant\n\nWould you like specific tips for improving answer quality?",
